overview: The user initiated a project to build a sleep questionnaire
  application, requiring database integration for responses, a client-facing
  dashboard, and authentication. The agent first assessed the existing codebase,
  identifying the need for a new database schema, API endpoints for data
  handling, and an admin interface. Key decisions included using NeonDB
  (PostgreSQL) for the database and implementing a simple password-based
  authentication. The authentication system was later refined to leverage
  Next.js middleware for a cleaner and more efficient route protection. The
  agent guided the user through setting up the database connection string and
  executed the Prisma migration to establish the necessary tables, ensuring all
  core functionalities were in place for data storage and access.
